        "label": "Dwolla application client ID and client secret",
        "generateUrl": "https://dashboard-sandbox.dwolla.com/",
        "setup": "Log in to the [Dwolla Sandbox Dashboard](https://dashboard-sandbox.dwolla.com/) (or your production dashboard) and open **Applications** to find your `client_id` and `client_secret`. The sandbox automatically creates an application when you sign up via the [sandbox account signup](https://accounts-sandbox.dwolla.com/sign-up). Use these client credentials to request an OAuth access token with `grant_type=client_credentials` as described in [Making Requests and Authentication](https://developers.dwolla.com/docs/api-reference/api-fundamentals/making-requests-and-authentication). Treat the `client_secret` like a password and store it securely.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "dwolla_access_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Dwolla OAuth application access token",
        "generateUrl": "https://developers.dwolla.com/docs/api-reference/tokens/create-an-application-access-token",
        "setup": "Generate a bearer access token by exchanging your Dwolla application's `client_id` and `client_secret` at the [`/token` endpoint](https://developers.dwolla.com/docs/api-reference/tokens/create-an-application-access-token) using the OAuth 2.0 client credentials flow. Dwolla documents this in [Making Requests and Authentication](https://developers.dwolla.com/docs/api-reference/api-fundamentals/making-requests-and-authentication). For sandbox development, you can first create an account at the [sandbox signup page](https://accounts-sandbox.dwolla.com/sign-up); the sandbox also lets you generate a token from the Applications tab in the [Sandbox Dashboard](https://dashboard-sandbox.dwolla.com/applications-legacy). Tokens expire after about one hour and must be regenerated.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      }
